SIMPLE: presto
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presto
<hw>Pres"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[It. or Sp.
<ets>presto</ets> quick, quickly. See <er>Prest</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Quickly; immediately; in haste;
suddenly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Presto</qex>! begone! 'tis here again.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Quickly; rapidly; -- a direction
for a quick, lively movement or performance; quicker than allegro, or
any rate of time except prestissimo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prestriction</ent>⟦br⟧
